00:00:00.710 --> 00:00:04.150
When we first started talking
about central tendencies and

00:00:04.150 --> 00:00:07.180
how we measure average, we
talked about the arithmetic

00:00:07.180 --> 00:00:09.360
mean and there you just added
up the numbers and you

00:00:09.360 --> 00:00:11.320
divided by the number
of numbers there were.

00:00:11.320 --> 00:00:16.040
So let's say our population
of numbers is-- we have a 3.

00:00:16.040 --> 00:00:20.110
Let's say we have three
3's, a 4, and a 5.

00:00:20.110 --> 00:00:21.480
That's our population.

00:00:21.480 --> 00:00:24.990
And if we wanted the population
mean here we were just

00:00:24.990 --> 00:00:25.990
add all the numbers up.

00:00:25.990 --> 00:00:32.140
We'd say 3 plus 3 plus
3 plus 4 plus 5.

00:00:32.140 --> 00:00:34.630
And then we would divide
that sum by the number

00:00:34.630 --> 00:00:36.750
of numbers we have.

00:00:36.750 --> 00:00:40.250
We would divide that by 5.

00:00:40.250 --> 00:00:41.200
And we would come--let's see.

00:00:41.200 --> 00:00:42.170
What would this be?

00:00:42.170 --> 00:00:46.160
This would be 9 plus
9; it'd be 18/5.

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:51.650
That would be 18/5,
which would be what?

00:00:51.650 --> 00:00:55.180
3 and 3/5, which is 3.6.

00:00:55.180 --> 00:00:57.980
It's a population mean for
this population of numbers.

00:00:57.980 --> 00:01:00.270
If we just rearranged the math
here a little bit we could view

00:01:00.270 --> 00:01:02.200
it a slightly different way.

00:01:02.200 --> 00:01:03.460
How many 3's do we have?

00:01:03.460 --> 00:01:09.410
We have three 3's, so we could
view this as 3 times 3.

00:01:09.410 --> 00:01:10.760
How many 4's do we have?

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:15.470
We have one 4, so
it's plus 1 times 4.

00:01:15.470 --> 00:01:16.950
Plus 1 time 5.

00:01:19.710 --> 00:01:22.610
All of that divided by 5.

00:01:22.610 --> 00:01:24.820
And then what we could do
is, this is the same thing.

00:01:24.820 --> 00:01:27.840
And I'm just doing a little
bit of basic really,

00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:28.790
number manipulation here.

00:01:28.790 --> 00:01:36.130
This is the same thing as
1/5 times 3 times 3 plus

00:01:36.130 --> 00:01:40.570
1 times 4 plus 1 times 5.

00:01:40.570 --> 00:01:44.110
And if we distribute this
1/5 this is equal to what?

00:01:44.110 --> 00:01:49.970
3/5 times 3 plus 1/5 times 1.

00:01:49.970 --> 00:01:56.310
So it's plus 1/5 times
4 plus 1/5 times 5.

00:01:59.320 --> 00:02:01.010
And this we can see in a
bunch of different ways.

00:02:01.010 --> 00:02:03.860
Let me express
these as decimals.

00:02:03.860 --> 00:02:05.170
So 3/5.

00:02:05.170 --> 00:02:17.160
So it's 0.6 times 3 plus 0.2
times 4 plus 0.2 times 5.

00:02:17.160 --> 00:02:19.800
Or we could express these
decimals as percentage.

00:02:19.800 --> 00:02:29.050
We could say 60% times 3, plus
20%-- sorry, 20% times 4.

00:02:29.050 --> 00:02:33.250
Plus 20% times 5.

00:02:33.250 --> 00:02:36.570
This is identical to adding up
the numbers and then dividing

00:02:36.570 --> 00:02:39.280
